/*!

<!---------------------------------------------------------------------------->

\mainpage Overview of the CUDA_Utils package
\author Seth R Johnson

This package contains C++ adapters and utilities for working with CUDA. It is
usable even if the CUDA runtime is not installed or supported on the current
platform. The Device class is meant to cleanly provide an interface for
determining whether CUDA is currently usable, and if so, to provide statistics
about the available graphics card (device).

Because all of the headers include \c <cuda_runtime.h> , it's not necessary to
compile this library with \c nvcc . It doesn't use any CUDA language
extensions: just API functions. It can however be linked into nvcc-compiled
libraries down the chain (and used by .cu and .cuh files).

<!---------------------------------------------------------------------------->

